      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ACE'S FOUR BRIAN (1) finds it hard to break through. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when second (29.94) at The Gardens. Solid record at the distance winning two races. One of the leading chances. CYCLONE ETHICS (2) was in the placings last time but three back produced a superb 19.05 win over 340m at Bulli. Expecting another bold showing. BRAILEY BANNER (8) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 22.25 beating Semi Peakin'. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Must be included in calculations. QUICK THINKIN' (6) was strongly fancied on the back of a win two starts ago but finished fifth last time (30.62) at Gosford. Won at his only start from this draw.",
